  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Helen Eliza Benson Garrison regrets that she was not able to attend Henry Egbert Benson&apos;s obsequies. Regarding Henry E. Benson&apos;s death, William Lloyd Garrison believes: &quot;But we must not mourn as do those who repine at the decrees of Heaven. All is right, for God has done it.&quot; William L. Garrison escaped injury in a broken down car. Henry E. Benson&apos;s death will be treated at greater length in the next issue of the Liberator.</subfield>
  </datafield>
